trans-unit.source: gtk_widget_child_focus() is called by widgets as the user moves around the window using keyboard shortcuts. direction indicates what kind of motion is taking place (up, down, left, right, tab forward, tab backward). gtk_widget_child_focus() calls the GtkWidgetClass.focus() vfunc; widgets override this vfunc in order to implement appropriate focus behavior.
